教學目標(中文)

本課程介紹經濟學派的演進，討論重要學派代表人物的思想內涵，進而幫助同學對於經濟學理論成立的時代背景有深入的認知。The main goal in 
this class is to discuss the economic thinking of some of the greatest minds of 
the modern era, such as Adam Smith, John Stuart Mill, David Hume, Karl Marx, 
Thomas Malthus, and John Maynard Keynes. Learning about the lives and ideas of 
these people is valuable in itself. But this course will also serve other 
purposes. It will be a way of acquiring a deeper understanding of economics for 
those who have taken economics courses 
before. 





教學目標(英文)

 





